Tiffany & Co. posted quarterly sales that missed projections as concerns about foreign tourist spending persisted. The shares fell as much as 3.7% in early trading. Same-store sales, a key retail metric, fell 3% globally, excluding currency swings, Tiffany said Wednesday. Analysts had estimated a 1.5% drop, according to Consensus Metrix. Key insights Market reaction Tiffany shares fell as low as $79.62 in premarket trading. They had risen 2.7% this year through Tuesday’s close, underperforming the benchmark S&P 500 Index. © 2019 Bloomberg L.P.